Class DualHashMap<K,V>

  • java.lang.Object
    • DualHashMap<K,V>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    DualMap<K,V>

    public class DualHashMap<K,V>
extends Object
implements DualMap<K,V>
    A DualHashMap is a HashMap implementation of the DualMap class. It maintains two HashMap variables and implements the functions put, remove, get, and reverseGet.
    Author:
    Paul Szyller

      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      V get(K key)
      Returns the value associated with the desired key.
      void put(K key, V value)
      Inserts a key and corresponding value into the DualHashMap, if either the key, the value, or both is already contained in the DualHashMap, the old association(s) will be removed.
      void remove(K key, V value)
      This method removes the mapping(s) for the desired key and value.
